text.tspan: Brazilian researcher is listed among the top 10 names of nature magazine in 2016
The magazine Nature, one of the world's most pres
tigious scientific publications, announced today its list of
the top 10 names in science in 2016. Among the chosen ones is the Brazilian Celina Maria Turchi Martelli. A retired
professor at the Federal University of Gois and a visiting researcher at the A
of the Oswaldo Cruz Foundation (Fiocruz) in Pernambuco, Celina leads the group that, for the first time, scientifically
associated the Zika virus infection in pregnant women and microcephaly cases in newborns.
